Mucius Scaevola, Pontifex Maximus, was a relative of Scaevola the Augur. He was a man of exalted character and great abilities both as a jurist and as an orator. He is said to have been the first Roman who wrote a systematic trea- tise on the Civil Law, and his work on that subject, in eighteen books, had great influence on succeeding jurists.
